  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I give my girlfriend space / stop the feeling of having my soul sucked out for the seconds I'm not with her?",
  "response": "It's completely normal to feel deeply attached to someone you love, but it's also crucial to maintain a healthy balance in any relationship. Giving your girlfriend space and managing your own feelings can be challenging, but here are some strategies that might help:\n\n1. **Set Clear Boundaries:** Establishing and respecting personal boundaries is key. Understand that both of you need time for yourselves, and this time apart can strengthen your relationship.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly:** Talk to your girlfriend about your feelings and your need for space. Make sure she understands that needing space doesn't mean you love her any less.\n\n3. **Stay Busy:** Engage in activities that you enjoy or pick up new hobbies. This will keep you occupied and help distract you from the constant thoughts about her.\n\n4. **Focus on Self-Care:** Spend time nurturing yourself. Exercise, meditate, read, or pursue your interests. Taking care of your mental and physical health will help you feel more balanced.\n\n5. **Lean on Friends and Family:** Spending time with other loved ones can provide a sense of support and fulfillment. Socializing with friends and family can be a good distraction and help you maintain a sense of normalcy outside of your romantic relationship.\n\n6. **Set Goals:** Work on personal goals or projects. This will help you feel accomplished and provide a sense of purpose that isn't solely tied to your relationship.\n\n7. **Practice Mindfulness:** Techniques like meditation can help you stay present and manage anxiety. Mindfulness can also help you cope with feelings of longing or dependence.\n\n8. **Understand Attachment Styles:** Learn about your attachment style to better understand why you feel the way you do. Attachment theory can offer insights into your behaviors and help you develop healthier ways to connect with your partner.\n\n9. **Limit Communication Frequency:** Gradually reduce the amount of time spent texting or calling. Setting specific times for communication can help you adjust to having more space.\n\n10. **Reflect and Journal:** Write down your thoughts and feelings to better understand them. Journaling can be a therapeutic way to express yourself and might help you gain insights into your emotions.\n\nUltimately, the goal is to balance your need for closeness with your need for independence. This can lead to a stronger, healthier relationship where both partners feel respected and fulfilled.",
